+# Review — CartView.jsx
+Task: `task-260421-182901-002`
+Chain: `pssk-cv-b2-b-260421-v5-260421-180935-50d2`
+
+Absolute writes to `C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/pipeline/...` were blocked by the workspace sandbox in this session. Local mirrors were written in `pages/PublicMenu`, and the prompt-specified findings fallback was written to `pages/Unknown/pssk-cv-b2-b-260421-v5-260421-180935-50d2-codex-findings.md`.
+
+## Findings
+1. [P1] Fix 6: Cancelled orders still inflate table and guest totals — `tableOrdersTotal` at `pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:521-530` sums every other guest order without `isCancelledOrder`, and Section 5 `guestTotal` at `pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:948-949` does the same. This keeps cancelled orders in the "Стол" totals even though `renderedTableTotal` already filters them at `pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:533-540`. FIX: add an early `if (isCancelledOrder(o)) return;` inside `tableOrdersTotal`, add `isCancelledOrder` to that memo's dependency array, and compute `guestTotal` with the same cancelled-order filter when Section 5 is flattened.
+2. [P1] Fix 2a: Pending orders never enter the pending bucket — the pending checks at `pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:467`, `pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:887`, and `pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:979` still compare the fallback status to `'submitted'`, but this batch defines Base44 new orders as `'new'`. As a result, the "Ожидает подтверждения" bucket stays empty and pending badges never render for fresh orders. FIX: change all three fallback comparisons from `'submitted'` to `'new'`.
+3. [P2] Fix 2b: Bucket render order is still reversed — `bucketOrder` at `pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:1094` is `['pending_unconfirmed', 'served', 'in_progress']`, so the pending bucket renders first instead of below "В работе" as required. FIX: reorder the array so `pending_unconfirmed` renders last, after `in_progress`.
+4. [P2] Fix 3: Terminal screen state is not durable across reloads — the V8 "Ничего не ждёте" branch at `pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:1014-1088` is driven only by live `statusBuckets` and `cart` state, and the file has no `terminalStateShownForVersion` state or localStorage read/write. That leaves the R4 durable terminal-state requirement unimplemented. FIX: introduce a versioned terminal-state key, hydrate it from `localStorage`, and persist `terminalStateShownForVersion` when the terminal screen becomes active without changing the locked UI.
+5. [P2] Fix 4: The "Стол" tab still uses a grouped accordion instead of flat guest cards — Section 5 at `pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:917-1003` renders a single wrapper `<Card>`, a `cart.table_orders` header button, and `otherGuestsExpanded` toggle logic around all guests. This is the exact grouped layout the fix is supposed to remove. FIX: replace the wrapper/accordion with `otherGuestIdsFromOrders.map((gid) => <Card key={gid}>...)` so each guest renders as its own flat card and the group button/header disappear.
+6. [P2] Fix 5: Empty-cart footer still shows the old primary CTA and lacks the help helper — the footer branch at `pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:1304-1310` keeps a filled button (`text-white` plus inline `backgroundColor`) for `cart.cta.back_to_menu`, and there is no `cart.cta.need_help_or_bill` helper line with an inline `<Bell>`. FIX: change this branch to an outline button with the same `onClick`, drop the inline background style, and add the helper paragraph with an inline bell icon below it.
+
+## Summary
+Total: 6 findings (0 P0, 2 P1, 4 P2, 0 P3)
+
+## Prompt Clarity
+- Overall clarity: 3
+- Ambiguous Fix descriptions (list Fix # and what was unclear): Fix 3 mixed a durable-state requirement with a UI that is already derivable from live buckets, so the persistence trigger/versioning rules had to be inferred from the root-cause text; the overall prompt also mixed "review only" instructions with full implementation steps.
+- Missing context (what info would have helped): the exact `terminalVersion` or localStorage key contract, and whether the local fallback path for started/progress/cc-analysis artifacts should mirror prior page-folder task files when the absolute pipeline path is sandbox-blocked.
+- Scope questions (anything you weren't sure if it's in scope): whether the report should flag the Fix 6 `guestTotal` issue only under Fix 6 or also repeat it under Fix 4, and whether the mandatory repo-sync step was intentionally required for a review-only chain step.
